{
  "texts": [
    "We study the patches produced by AutoCodeRover and report that 2/3 of the autonomously produced patches from AutoCodeRover are correct and acceptable.",
    "We note that this aspect has not been reported by Devin [24] and SWE-agent [47].2 Relevant Literature 2.",
    "Program RepairTest-suite based automated program repair (APR) has attracted significant attention in the last decade [13].",
    "These techniques aim to generate a patch for a buggy program to pass a given test-suite.",
    "APR techniques typically include search-based, semantic-based, and pattern/learning-based APR."
  ]
}